The practical course in internal medicine lasts 8 weeks and can be passed at one or in multiple internal medicine divisions. Addition to daily clinical work, the students have to train practical skills necessary for physician and to take part in seminars and conferences.
The subject deals with the investigation of the medical patient, investigations, diagnosis formulation, designing of the treatment plan, assessment of the treatment course and results, documentation of the data and their presentation. Within the course, the students have to fill in the diary of medical training and form epicrisis.
At least 100 corresponding AMBOSS platform cases must be solved during the internal medicine cycle, the completion will be checked up on at the end of the semester.Objectives/eesmärkid:  General aim of internal medicine practical course is to implement to practice the theoretical knowledge acquired during the studies. The course can be started after the completion of the mandatory clinical subjects of the 5th year. Aims: -	To use in the routine clinical work the basic clinical terminology, skills of interviewing and physical examination as well as to study the medical documentation; -	To learn general aspect of common internal diseases, to learn to simple investigations and monitoring of patients; -	To learn differential diagnostics of internal diseases and optimal application of diagnostic methods; -	To study contemporary internal medicine diseases treatment guidelines and individual options of the studied patients on the basis of literature data; -	To design of the management of individual patient including diagnostics, short- and long-term maintenance treatment, assessment of treatment targets and prognosis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: -	is able to take the anamnesis, examine patients with various internal diseases objectively, prescribe optimal diagnostic investigations and evaluate the results of the investigations; -	have learn general aspects common internal disease and able to analyse clinical symptoms of the disease and to establish final clinical diagnosis; -	knows the treatment algorithms and guidelines of long-term management of internal diseases; -	is able to present patient case to colleagues using appropriate medical terminology, to do necessary documentation and write an epicrisis (a critical or analytical summing up of a medical case history).
